title: Sylvester Shooting reveals 8th victim
content:
Sylvester Police now say an 8th teen was injured in a weekend shooting.
A 14-year old girl showed up at the police department yesterday with a wound to her toe.
Gunfire broke out about 12:30 Saturday morning at a party at the Royale Room on Highway 82.
18-year olds Keyona McKinney, Diamond Hooks, Quanderia Bentley and 17-year olds Zytavious Anderson and Shanteria Timmons were treated at a hospital and released.
Investigators refuse to identify two other injured juveniles, but we know they are okay.
Sylvester Police are interviewing possible suspects, but so far no arrests have been made.
